They are also quit of buckstalls‚ whilst the other residents ought to assemble for the purpose of collecting the deer into an inclosure which they have to make for that purpose, or if they fail to do so are heavily fined or compound. Also whenever any carts or waggons pass loaded through the forest, or horses with packs on their backs, the owners thereos are wont to pay the officers of the forest a greater or less sum for their right of passage, but they have ever, by virtue of the deed, been quit of making any payment in respect thereos.
